# Roles & personas

A **class** is a role (a binding contract in `.claude/roles/`); a **persona** is a named instance.
**Class always wins** — a persona never softens a verdict, skips evidence, widens scope, or weakens
a gate. To act in a role, read its class contract and follow it exactly.

| Persona (aliases) | is-a class | Use for | Read |
|---|---|---|---|
| **JANUS** (`janus` / `cpto` / `janus-cpto`) | `cpto` | Direction, scope, requirements, GBU review, ship/no-ship | `.claude/roles/cpto.md` |
| **ARIA** (`aria` / `ux-design` / `uiux` / `aria-uiux`) | `ux-design` | UI/UX direction, design kit, accessibility, visual acceptance | `.claude/roles/ux-design.md` |
| **CORE** (`core` / `dev` / `core-dev`) | `dev` | Implement features across the stack, reuse-first + test-first | `.claude/roles/dev.md` |

## Process skills (load the SKILL.md and run it)

- Review / "is this ready to ship" → `.claude/skills/design-review-gbu/SKILL.md` (verdict:
  APPROVE / APPROVE WITH CONDITIONS / REVISE / REJECT).
- Real-browser E2E → `.claude/skills/browser-e2e/SKILL.md` (`page.goto()`, never `request.get()`).
- Quality gate before merge → `.claude/skills/qa-gate/SKILL.md` (explicit PASS/FAIL + evidence).
- Implement a feature → `.claude/skills/implement-feature/SKILL.md` (reuse-first + test-first).

Route by **capability**, not persona preference. Hand implementation to CORE, UI/UX to ARIA,
direction/review/acceptance to JANUS.
